&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At South Star, we are committed to empowering businesses in the telecom sector by providing comprehensive support and management solutions for their IT infrastructure. Based in Navi Mumbai, we specialize in offering a wide range of services, including application environment support, IT infrastructure environment management, network monitoring, end-user support, and service design &amp;amp; monitoring. Our focus on the telecom sector allows us to deliver exceptional results that are tailored to our unique clients.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: MDM Administrator (Endpoint &amp;amp; Device Management)- Night Shift, Mumbai&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&lt;/strong&gt; South Star Software Pvt. Ltd.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Mumbai / Navi Mumbai&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3–4 Years (L1/L2 blend)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting To:&lt;/strong&gt; IT Operations / Endpoint Management Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Star Software is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;MDM Administrator&lt;/strong&gt; to manage and support the organization’s &lt;strong&gt;enterprise mobile and endpoint management environment&lt;/strong&gt;. The role focuses on &lt;strong&gt;device onboarding, policy enforcement, compliance monitoring, application deployment, and user support&lt;/strong&gt; across corporate‑owned and BYOD endpoints, using industry‑standard MDM/UEM platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device &amp;amp; Endpoint Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enroll, configure, and manage &lt;strong&gt;mobile devices and endpoints&lt;/strong&gt; across supported platforms (smartphones, tablets, laptops, desktops).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform &lt;strong&gt;device lifecycle activities&lt;/strong&gt; including provisioning, reassignment, remote lock/wipe, and decommissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support both &lt;strong&gt;corporate‑owned and BYOD&lt;/strong&gt; device models as per policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;User Support &amp;amp; Ticket Handling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide &lt;strong&gt;L1/L2 support&lt;/strong&gt; for MDM‑related issues raised via ITSM tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot common problems such as enrollment failures, app access issues, policy conflicts, and profile errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate complex platform, policy, or security issues to senior engineers with complete diagnostics and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with audits by providing compliance and inventory reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate &lt;strong&gt;device inventory and compliance records&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare regular reports on &lt;strong&gt;enrollment status, device health, and policy adherence&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain SOPs, user guides, and knowledge base articles related to MDM operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with &lt;strong&gt;any enterprise MDM / UEM solution&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of &lt;strong&gt;endpoint management concepts&lt;/strong&gt; and device lifecycle management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;mobile OS and endpoint platforms&lt;/strong&gt; (smartphones, desktops, laptops).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of &lt;strong&gt;directory services and identity management&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
