&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Star is seeking a dedicated Receivables Support Analyst to join our Accounts Receivable Team. This role is pivotal in ensuring efficient customer service-driven collections, conducting billing analysis, and resolving payment-related issues. The ideal candidate will leverage their expertise to manage a portfolio of U.S.-based customers, focusing on collaboration and customer satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile and distribute daily/monthly performance reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review daily payments and conduct payment investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor online payment transactions and support company bill pay center.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce and present monthly performance reports for the bill pay center.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with outside collection placements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Receivables VP, Director, and the team as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate to advanced Excel skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in report design and presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent English verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional time management and follow-up skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently with self-motivation, while also thriving in a team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to excellence and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work U.S. Eastern Standard Time hours (8:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2-5 years of experience in collections, finance, and/or customer service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

